HEADWORD: Hasty pudding
<hw>Has"ty pud"ding</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧s"t⟦ycr⟧ p⟦usdot⟧d"d⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A thick batter pudding made of Indian meal stirred into
boiling water; mush.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A batter or pudding made of flour or oatmeal,
stirred into boiling water or milk.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hat</ent>⟦br⟧
